Fidel Castro is shown here in the Cuban jungle in 1957 with a small group of his staff and their Raoul. Two years later, Castro's forces toppled the existing government and elevated Fidel to the nation's leadershin whp k eir revo utionary forces. Kneeling in the foreground is Castro's brother P, wnere he remained for almost fifty years. (© Bettmann/Corbis)
